UNITED STATES of America, Complainant-Appellee, v. LAI SEE, Defendant-Appellant. No. 119. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Oct. 15, 1934. Edward A. Welti, of New York City (Herbert S. Siegal, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Martin Conboy, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Irvin C. Rutter, Asst.' U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order (6 F. Supp. 629) affirmed.
